  "texts": [
    "(2) Search for explicit data licences.",
    "The annotator searches for a licence specifically given to the dataset (not the accompanying code) by the authors.",
    "A licence is found if (i) the GitHub repository mentions or links a licence in reference to the data, (ii) the Hugging Face licence label was uploaded by the dataset creator themselves or (iii) the paper, Hugging Face or Papers with Code provide a dataset-specific licence link, attributable to the data authors.",
    "(3) Identify a licence type.",
    "A licence may fall into a set of common types (for example, MIT, Apache 2, CC BY SA and so on), be a 'Custom' licence, a permission request form or, if none was found for the data, unspecified."
